modules.description: This module creates a session manager that handles session lifecycle operations using a custom backend and cookie-based session identifiers. It provides functions to load sessions from a backend using a key or HTTP headers, generate new sessions, update session values or expiration, and clear sessions, with support for cookie header generation and management. It works with backend-specific types for keys, values, and expiration periods, and is used to manage authenticated user sessions in web applications by tying session state to HTTP cookies.

This module defines the interface for managing session cookies in a backend system. It provides operations to generate, retrieve, update, and delete session keys with associated values and expiration periods. It works with string-based keys and values, and expiration times represented as 64-bit integers, suitable for implementing session management in web applications where persistent or temporary session tracking is required.

This module manages session state using cookies, providing functions to load, create, update, and expire sessions backed by a custom storage type. It handles session keys, values, and expiration periods, generating appropriate HTTP headers for cookie management. Concrete use cases include authenticating users via session cookies, tracking session state across requests, and securely expiring sessions after a specified time.

This module provides a signature for managing session cookies with operations to create, validate, and expire cookies using string identifiers and time values. It supports building session management systems that tie session state to HTTP cookies, enabling authenticated user sessions in web applications. The child modules implement concrete session managers with custom backends, offering functions to load, generate, update, and clear sessions while handling cookie header generation. Together, they enable secure session handling with support for storage-specific types and expiration policies.
